TopicTitle: Lots of lag in career save compared to science/sandbox

Articles.Content:
Hi all,

I've been trying to play some more KSP lately and started up a career save. After playing a bit I started a sandbox save and the FPS are so much higher. Just wondering if anyone knows why that might be.

My career save gets around 5fps at the KSC and 25fps when controlling a 50 part vessel. Sandbox gets 60fps at KSC and 55fps with the same vessel.

I understand that career mode may have more data to process in terms of life support, etc but this feels like a massive difference.

Game version is 1.12.3.

There could totally be a mod that is just causing all of this, but it's been a while since I've played and am rusty with the logs... Thank you!
